so to those who have visited a grave site what exactly do you do there and what feeling are you left with after you have visited im not trying to be cold yet i truely don't understand it depends if it is of older relatives then it is likely different for siblings spouses or children to me it is just a place to stop and think maybe to remember a bit time to smile at my great aunts comment about the tree on our plot getting hit by lightning to late and missed anyhow or my grandfather with the shrapnel still in his body from wwi my grandmother and her last words to me on her death bed get a job you bum i was had enough money to not work for three years and had just come back from southern mexico thank you it is time to go visit them again my father died years ago and my mother will be going soon my youngest brother is and the oldest yes miles to spend a day sitting under a lightning blasted tree thinking about the history of a non believing family over several hundred years only a few generations of which are buried there Family One Hundred Years of Solitude Knots Landing Jewish bereavement Hun-Apu One Tree Hill (TV series) Dancing at Lughnasa Pitaten EastEnders Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Japanese funeral Piccolo Junior Saga Fancy Crane Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Melanie Wilkes The Catcher in the Rye Comanche Emperor Yuan of Han Jacen Solo Charmed Algerian Family Code Social rule Blood purity (Harry Potter) Funeral Back to the Future timeline Incest Neighbours The Curse of Fenric Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Paul Is Dead Charles Dickens Michael Jackson Ocean's Twelve The Amber Spyglass W.I.T.C.H. Sleeping Murder Sin City Kurt Cobain Zhao Yun Order of succession Mary of Teck Anakin Solo Ten Commandments Luke Skywalker Jaina Solo The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Kodocha John Lennon USS Alfred A. Cunningham (DD-752) Days of our Lives Emperor Ling of Han Grief Tenchi Muyo! Jei Predestination paradox Alois Hitler British Royal Family Louise of H